

mimeto7bit(1M)                                     mimeto7bit(1M)

SSyynnooppssiiss
       /usr/lib/mail/surrcmd/mimeto7bit < mime-message > encoded-
       mime-message

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       mimeto7bit is used by the  mail  SMTP  system  to  convert
       non-7-bit  MIME  messages  into  7-bit MIME messages.  The
       mail message, read from standard input,  must  be  a  MIME
       message  (mime-message).   Any  parts  of the message that
       have a Content-Transfer-Encoding heading of 8bit or binary
       will  have  its  contents converted to quoted-printable or
       base64, respectively.

       If the message is not a MIME message, the conversion  will
       fail.

       The converted message is written to standard output.

